    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/15/jake-armsey-notches-multi-hit-day-and-kenan-bowman-hits-first-career-long-ball-as-baseball-drops-series-finale-against-high-point-sunday",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SPARTANBURG, S.C. \u2013\nClosing a series fitted for late May rather than early March, USC Upstate baseball and High Point delivered a three-game set with a postseason feel this weekend at Cleveland S. Harley Park, battling until the very end in Sunday's finale. Going for the sweep, the Spartans dropped the series' third game in the late innings, falling 9-7 to the Panthers.\nSunday's game saw momentum come in waves as the two sides answered one another's punches with a counterpunch, seeing the lead change hands twice and tied twice. High Point landed the first blow, scratching a run without a hit in the first. However, Upstate responded in the second inning as redshirt sophomore rightfielder\nKenan Bowman\nlaunched his first career home run, a three-run blast to center.\nThe Panthers rallied with single tallies in the fourth and fifth to tie things at the game's midpoint before Upstate answered with two runs in the home half of the fifth, using a wild pitch and sac fly from fifth-year senior designated hitter\nJohnny Sweeney\n. High Point fought back, plating two in the following half inning before scoring the go-ahead runs in the eighth for the victory.\nBowman secured the Spartans' lone multi-RBI game, tying for the team lead with his fourth such game this season. Redshirt senior third baseman\nJake Armsey\nregistered Upstate's lone multi-hit game as his two hits extended his team-long hitting streak and reached base streak to seven and 10 games, respectively.\nMaking his first weekend start, redshirt junior right-handed pitcher\nMax Eichenberger\ntied his career high, striking out five over a career-long-tying 3.0 innings of work. Out of the bullpen, sophomore left-hander\nMax Kaplan\nturned in his longest relief outing of the season\u2014in his third appearance of the week\u2014with 2.0 scoreless innings of work.\nGame Information\nScore: High Point 7; USC Upstate 5\nRecords: USC Upstate (10-11; 2-1 Big South); High Point (11-9; 1-2 BSC)\nLocation: Cleveland S. Harley Park | Spartanburg, S.C.\nHow It Happened\nT1: Hanging the first run on the board, High Point used back-to-back groundouts to produce a run, the RBI going to Landen Johnson.\nB2: Putting the Spartans in front,\nKenan Bowman\nlaunched a three-run shot to the deepest part of the ballpark in center.\nT4: Getting a run back, Johnson slugged a solo homer to right-center for the Panthers.\nT5: Battling back to knot the contest, Jack Clark produced High Point's third tally with a single to right-center.\nB5: Breaking the deadlock, Upstate scored a pair in the fifth. The first came as\nJake Armsey\nscampered home on a wild pitch before\nJohnny Sweeney\ndrove home\nTyler Lang\nwith a sac fly.\nT6: Fighting back once more, the Panthers tied the game behind a Jace Kohler RBI single and an RBI fielder's choice from Frank Kelly.\nT8: Pulling a ball down the rightfield line, Willie Ponce drove home the final two High Point runs with an RBI triple.\nNotable\nBehind\nKenan Bowman's\nsecond-inning, three-run blast, Upstate scored its first runs of all three games with a home run, following a two-run homer from\nWylie Waters\non Friday and a three-run shot from\nMaloy Heaghney\non Saturday.\nBowman's homer marked the first of his collegiate career as he became the third Spartan this season to hit his first career Division I home run in a Spartan uniform, joining\nClayton Campidilli\nand Heaghney.\nUp Next for the Spartans\nReturning to the road, Upstate begins a five-game road swing next Wednesday at Charlotte. The Spartans and 49ers meet for a 6 p.m. ET first pitch.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!"
